<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 02 at 3:59AM EDT  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Calhoun, western
Gilmer, southeastern Wirt, northern Roane and east central Jackson
Counties through 430 AM EDT...
At 359 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Spencer, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Spencer, Grantsville, Arnoldsburg, Cedar Creek State Park, Shock,
Millstone, Mount Zion, Newberne, Orma, Big Springs, Nicut, Stumptown,
Tanner, Annamoriah, Gay and Normantown.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
